two functions must be written
-----------------------------

write predicate functions. predicate abstracts the pattern. (handles program logic)
recursion handles the arithmetic functionality of the program



sum
---

template <typename T>

T sum(T *p, size_t start, size_t end){
if (start == end) { return p[start]; }
return p[start] + sum(p, ++start, end);

template <typename T>
T sum(T *p, size_t n) {return sum(p, 0, n-1); } 



